---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import ParallaxBanner from '../../components/ParallaxBanner.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
import { articleSchema, breadcrumbSchema } from '../../lib/schema';

const pageTitle = 'New Construction Homes in New Braunfels, TX | Cody Posey';
const pageDescription = 'Explore new construction homes and builder communities in New Braunfels, TX. Learn builder incentives, timelines, upgrades, and what to know before you sign.';
const pageSchema = [
  articleSchema({ title: pageTitle, description: pageDescription, url: '/new-braunfels/new-construction' }),
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'New Braunfels', url: '/new-braunfels' },
    { name: 'New Construction', url: '/new-braunfels/new-construction' },
  ]),
];
---

<Layout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDescription}
  schema={pageSchema}
>
  <Navbar />
  <main style="padding-top: 80px;">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="nb-hero">
      <div class="nb-hero__overlay"></div>
      <div class="nb-hero__content">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/new-braunfels/">New Braunfels</a> <span>/</span> <span>New Construction</span>
        </nav>
        <h1>New <span style="color:#FF1616;">Construction</span></h1>
        <p>Builder communities, new developments, and what to know before buying new</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Overview -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="nc-intro__grid">
          <div>
            <h2>New Builds in <span class="accent">New Braunfels</span></h2>
            <p>New construction is a major part of the New Braunfels housing market. The city's growth — driven by its location between Austin and San Antonio — has attracted national and regional builders who are developing master-planned communities across the north and south sides of the city.</p>
            <p>Buying new construction is a different process than buying resale. Builders have their own contracts, timelines, and sales teams. Having your own representation matters — and it doesn't cost you anything extra.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Benefits & Tradeoffs -->
    <section class="section" style="background: var(--light-gray);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Benefits & <span class="accent">Tradeoffs</span></h2>
        </div>
        <div class="nc-compare__grid">
          <div class="nc-compare__card">
            <h3>Why Buyers Choose New Construction</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Everything is new — no deferred maintenance</li>
              <li>Modern floor plans and energy efficiency</li>
              <li>Builder warranties (structural, mechanical, cosmetic)</li>
              <li>Ability to choose finishes, colors, and upgrades</li>
              <li>Community amenities (pools, trails, playgrounds)</li>
              <li>Builder incentives and rate buydowns</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="nc-compare__card">
            <h3>What to Consider</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Timelines can shift — builds take 4-8+ months</li>
              <li>Base prices don't include upgrades or lot premiums</li>
              <li>Landscaping is often minimal at closing</li>
              <li>Newer communities may lack mature trees and shade</li>
              <li>HOA fees and restrictions vary by community</li>
              <li>Builder contracts favor the builder — get your own agent</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Major Communities -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Major <span class="accent">Communities</span></h2>
          <p>Some of the active new construction communities in and around New Braunfels</p>
        </div>
        <div class="nc-communities__grid">
          <div class="nc-community">
            <h3>Veramendi</h3>
            <p>A 2,400-acre mixed-use development located between Highway 46 and River Road. Veramendi includes over 480 acres of parkland with miles of walking and cycling trails. The Ledge amenity center features a 25,000 sq ft complex with a resort-style pool, splash pad, pavilions, and poolside kitchen. Builders include Brightland Homes, Coventry Homes, David Weekley Homes, Highland Homes, Perry Homes, Pulte Homes, Scott Felder Homes, Drees Custom Homes, and others. Homes range from the high $300s to mid-$500Ks. Zoned to New Braunfels ISD with an on-site elementary school and a second NBISD elementary campus planned.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="nc-community">
            <h3>Vintage Oaks</h3>
            <p>A 3,900-acre master-planned community located west of New Braunfels off Highway 46 in the Texas Hill Country. Vintage Oaks is a build-on-your-lot community with homesites ranging from 1 to 14 acres. Buyers can choose their own builder or select a completed custom home. Amenities include a Tuscan-style clubhouse, Olympic-size pool, lazy river, fitness facility, 5-mile hiking trail, tennis and volleyball courts, and a regulation soccer field. Multiple neighborhoods within the community include The Grove, Bear Creek, The Bluffs, Timber Ridge, and others. Homesites are priced from the low $180Ks, with finished home prices varying by builder and lot.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="nc-community">
            <h3>Meyer Ranch</h3>
            <p>A 700-acre master-planned community located at 9666 W. Highway 46, built on a former working cattle ranch. Builders include Gehan Homes, Highland Homes, Chesmar Homes, and Scott Felder Homes, with homes starting from the high $390s. Amenities include a splash pad, fitness center, dog park, putting green, playgrounds, an amphitheater, community green with fire pits, and Hilltop Park with trails and butterfly gardens. Zoned to Comal ISD — Bill Brown Elementary, Smithson Valley Middle School, and Smithson Valley High School.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="nc-community">
            <h3>Mayfair</h3>
            <p>New master-planned community on the north side developed by SouthStar Communities. Over 300 acres of parks and open space, 35+ miles of planned trails, and a new Comal ISD elementary school already open with four more campuses planned. Homes start from the $290s. A commercial district — Midtown Mayfair — is planned for shopping, dining, and workspaces.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="nc-community">
            <h3>Legacy at Lake Dunlap</h3>
            <p>Located along the shores of Lake Dunlap near Highway 46 with builders including Toll Brothers, Pulte Homes, Monticello Homes, Highland Homes, and Drees Custom Homes. Homes start in the high $300Ks with floor plans from approximately 1,637 to 3,925 sq ft. Amenities include private lake access, community docks, pickleball courts, trails, and Guadalupe River access. Served by Comal ISD.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="nc-community">
            <h3>Other Active Communities</h3>
            <p>New communities are being announced regularly as the New Braunfels area continues to grow. Builders are actively developing along Highway 46, FM 1044, Klein Road, and other corridors. Reach out for the most current list of active new construction options in your price range and preferred area.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Builder Considerations -->
    <section class="section" style="background: var(--light-gray);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Builder <span class="accent">Considerations</span></h2>
        </div>
        <div class="nc-builder__grid">
          <div class="nc-builder__item">
            <h3>Bring Your Own Agent</h3>
            <p>The builder's sales team represents the builder, not you. Having your own agent ensures someone is reviewing the contract, tracking the build, and negotiating on your behalf. This doesn't cost you extra — the builder pays the commission.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="nc-builder__item">
            <h3>Understand the True Cost</h3>
            <p>Base price is the starting point. Lot premiums, structural options, design center upgrades, and closing costs can add 10-20% or more to the advertised price. I can help you evaluate the real cost before you commit.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="nc-builder__item">
            <h3>Know the Timeline</h3>
            <p>New builds typically take 4-8 months from contract to close, depending on the builder and stage of construction. Pre-construction homes may take longer. Move-in ready inventory homes are available if you need to close faster.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq-section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About New Construction</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Do I need my own agent when buying new construction?</summary>
            <p>Yes, and it is free to you. The builder pays the agent commission whether you have representation or not. Without your own agent, the only person at the table working on your behalf is you. The builder's sales team represents the builder's interests — not yours. Your agent reviews contracts, monitors construction quality, negotiates on your behalf, and ensures the builder delivers what was promised.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What builder incentives are currently available in New Braunfels?</summary>
            <p>Builder incentives change frequently and vary by community and builder. Common incentives include interest rate buydowns, closing cost contributions, free upgrades, and reduced lot premiums on inventory homes. Some builders offer more aggressive incentives on homes that are completed or near completion. I stay current on available incentives across all active communities and can help you identify the best deals.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How long does it take to build a new home?</summary>
            <p>Build times in the New Braunfels area typically range from four to eight months from contract to closing, depending on the builder and the stage of construction when you purchase. Pre-construction homes that have not started building may take longer. If you need to move in quickly, many communities have inventory homes that are completed or nearly completed and ready for a faster closing timeline.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section" style="background: #000; color: #fff; text-align: center;">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Interested in <span class="accent">New Construction</span>?</h2>
        <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); max-width: 600px; margin: 1rem auto 2rem;">I can walk you through the active communities, help you compare builders, and represent you through the process at no additional cost.</p>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
          <a href="https://a.nhb.app/u/cposeyrealestate" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-primary">Search New Construction</a>
          <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-outline">Tour New Construction Homes</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <ParallaxBanner image="/images/generated/guadalupe-river.png" />

  <ContactForm context="I'm interested in touring new construction..." />
  <Footer />

  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do I need my own agent when buying new construction?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, and it is free to you. The builder pays the commission whether you have representation or not. Without your own agent, the only person working on your behalf is you."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What builder incentives are currently available in New Braunfels?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Common incentives include interest rate buydowns, closing cost contributions, free upgrades, and reduced lot premiums. Incentives change frequently and vary by community and builder."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does it take to build a new home?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Build times typically range from four to eight months from contract to closing. Inventory homes that are completed or near completion can close faster."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>
</Layout>

<style>
  .nb-hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 280px;
    background: url('/images/generated/home-nb-modern.png') center/cover no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .nb-hero__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.55);
  }

  .nb-hero__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .nb-hero__content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .nb-hero__content p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .breadcrumb span {
    margin: 0 0.3rem;
  }

  /* Intro */
  .nc-intro__grid p {
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  /* Compare Grid */
  .nc-compare__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .nc-compare__card {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }

  .nc-compare__card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .nc-compare__card ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .nc-compare__card li {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding: 0.4rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .nc-compare__card li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.85rem;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    background: #FF1616;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  /* Communities */
  .nc-communities__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .nc-community {
    border: 1px solid var(--light-gray);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
  }

  .nc-community:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  .nc-community h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .nc-community p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Builder */
  .nc-builder__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .nc-builder__item {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }

  .nc-builder__item h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .nc-builder__item p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .faq-section { padding: 4rem 0; background: #f9f9f9; }
  .faq-section h2 { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .faq-list { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .faq-item { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #eee; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .faq-item summary { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .faq-item summary::after { content: '+'; font-size: 1.3rem; color: #FF1616; font-weight: 700; }
  .faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '\2212'; }
  .faq-item p { padding: 0 1.5rem 1.25rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 0.95rem; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .nc-compare__grid,
    .nc-communities__grid,
    .nc-builder__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
